You first look for the first letter in the string, then you simply take the substring until its index.

If you want what is before the first occurrence of a letter, you could use a capturing group to match any char except a letter using `\P{L}` and then match a letter using `\p{L}`.

    ^(\P{L}+)\p{L}

- `^` Start of string
- `(` Capture **group 1**
 - `\P{L}+` Match 1+ times the opposite of `\p{L}`
- `)`
- `\p{L}` Match any letter from any language

[Regex demo](https://regex101.com/r/JpvJTG/1) | [Java demo](http://ideone.com/m5tLyw)

