`container` and `infoStyle` are just objects which dictate some style.

The `animations.css` just has the animations required to make the `CSSTransition` work:


```lang-css
.fade-enter, .fade-appear {
    opacity: 0;
}

.fade-enter-active {
    opacity: 1;
    transition: opacity 600ms linear 400ms;
}

.fade-exit {
    opacity: 1;
}

.fade-exit-active {
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 400ms linear;
}


.crunch-enter, .crunch-appear {
    height: 0%;
}

.crunch-enter-active {
    height: 100%;
    transition: all 600ms ease-out 400ms;
}

.crunch-exit {
    height: 100%;
}

.crunch-exit-active {
    height: 0%;
    transition: all 400ms ease-in
}
